=head1 DESCRIPTION

Subslot elicitation settings.

C<DefaultValueSpecification> is a list of default values for a
constituent sub slot in a composite slot. Default values are used when
Amazon Lex hasn't determined a value for a slot. You can specify
default values from context variables, session attributes, and defined
values. This is similar to C<DefaultValueSpecification> for slots.

C<PromptSpecification> is the prompt that Amazon Lex uses to elicit the
sub slot value from the user. This is similar to C<PromptSpecification>
for slots.

